:::summary
Astrophysics is the branch of science that applies the laws of physics and chemistry to understand the nature, origin, and evolution of stars, galaxies, and the universe itself. It is one of the most awe-inspiring fields of human inquiry — probing questions as profound as the age and origin of the cosmos, the nature of black holes, and the ultimate fate of the universe. For the Christian, astrophysics is an act of wonder before the majesty of God's creation: "The heavens declare the glory of God, and the sky above proclaims his handiwork" (Psalm 19:1).
:::

